In answer to your question though, while in some ways it is good, it is also bad in some ways. There is no real fear of failure now at any level. You can try anything and pretty much be ready to go about your business again in 20-30 minutes with little loss other than a bit of time. For the good parts, it would be hard to explain unless you have experienced it. That experience is something they have taken away from the newer players, to those players detriment in my opinion. I don't say most zones should be like that, but there should definitely still be a few. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
