<br>
There are 2 ways to view content:<br>
1) How hard is the content to solve power-wise<br>
an easy mob for a lvl 60 char is still much harder than a hard mob for a lvl 2 char. That's absolute view, and it is a legitimate view. For some mobs, you need huge forces of high-level people, so yes, compared to Sebilis, for example, PoP tier 1 is <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">crap</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> hard, and that doesn't change even if lvl 45 people attempt Seb and lvl 65 do Tier 1 PoP...<br>
<br>
2) How hard is it to overcome the current content<br>
at level 65, Sebilis Myco is trivial compared to level 51 chef. That's subjective view, equally legitimate to the other view, but generally makes you feel EQ has gotten way easier. &quot;Convenience&quot;, for example, makes a huge difference in this view, whether in view 1, its mainly the mobs which make the difference, and the amount of people needed for it. Here, things as &quot;how many&quot; is very relative to the mob (Trakanon with 50 people is not harder than a Krup Warrior with 3), but things as &quot;how hard to manage&quot; play important roles.<br>
<br>
<br>
Or easier said: 10 deaths a 12 minutes downtime in 4 hours is hard in view 1, 1 death with 2 hours CR in 4 hours is hard in view 2...it's the same, but different things you feel as &quot;hard&quot;...<br>
<br>
And yes, i do count myself to number 2 - i miss those naked CRs, those feeling that you knew &quot;If i make <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">one</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> fault, we will be doing nothing except trying to get back here for the next 2 1/2 hours&quot;. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55795">Carighan Maconar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Enchantress of the 59th Circle<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Member of the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.nebelwelt.de/eq/index.htm">Namenlose Bruderschaft</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on Solusek Ro<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.mutedfaith.com/quiz/qz4.htm&quot;" target="&quot;new&quot;"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mutedfaith.com/images/time.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.mutedfaith.com/quiz/qz4.htm&quot;" target="&quot;new&quot;">find your element</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.mutedfaith.com&quot;" target="&quot;new&quot;">mutedfaith.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elyia>Elyia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 232<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/10/03 2:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ is dying</span