<br>
However i do see your point, although much of what the old school deems &quot;difficult&quot; i consider merely time consuming.  Lack of public transportation, lack of bind bots, presence of 8 hour nekkid CRs all fall into this category for me, i.e. things which aren't difficult or challenging, but time consuming and frustrating.  These are the things that make SOE's most valued customers, the low bandwidth using &quot;casual gameing&quot; cash cows, quit.<br>
<br>
As far as trivialization goes, EQ was doomed from the start by lack of item decay and hard level limits, as someone already pointed out.  Stuff gets handed down but only extremely rarely is it removed from a server.  Currency is devalued, items are devalued, and we end up with level 10 newbies who can afford to buy items which were once the best the game had to offer, and only rarely is there an item flag preventing them from equipping it.  At the same time, SOE has to keep a fresh carrot in front of the end game guilds, and so end game gear has to keep getting better.  There really is no solution for the gear problem in EQ, since they can't add item decay at this point or the general uproar would deafen us all.<br>
<br>
Encounter difficulty is effected by AA abilities more than anything i think.  Think about how trivial it is to buff a raid now, just MGB it, think about mana savings AAs and damage enhancing AAs, and characters are stronger than they have ever been.  Those skills trivialize content a thousand times worse than bind bots or teleport stones or researchable spells do, and the presence of such a large population of &quot;heroes&quot; in the world really does point to the end of EQ.  <br>
<br>
But gah it has to end sometime, they can't just keep tacking on a few levels and zones, can't just continue to append to its old ass code.  At some point, they have to say, &quot;enough is enough,&quot; and start a clean slate where certain deep errors in the structure of this game can be corrected.  Hello, EQ2. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.sillyjanine.com/mybases.html"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.cestusdei.org/uploads/images/luxysig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=telurinon>Telurinon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/10/03 3:29 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ is dying</span><hr size=1> 8 hour Corpse Recoveries are not fun.<br>
<br>
If someone who plays 8 hours a day can do something, this does not mean the player who only plays 2 hours a day can do it in 4 days.<br>
<br>
The PoP books are there to make life as a non-porting, non-bind-anywhere class better.  For years, I refused to pay people for ports.  I'd take the boat if I needed to get anywhere.  Now that I am playing a wizard, I wonder how I ever managed to get buy without ports...even the pop books are too slow for me.<br>
<br>
Yes, EQ is easier these days.  Some of it stems from mud-wimping while other bits come from them fixing some things that were just bad in the initial design.  Yes, this means that people who are less than skilled at the game reach the high end content.  Yes, this means Dreadlands type OOC banal chatter in PoD.<br>
<br>
I bet half the people reading this thread still play, though, and most of them have 2 or more accounts.  EQ is not dying quite yet.  It is just adjusting to a more casual playstyle. <p><img src=http://home.socal.rr.com/fgrubb/images/Misc/tel_flame.gif><br><SELECT NAME=D1<br><OPTION SELECTED>Telurinon Aelvenborne, 55th Rake of Black Isle<br><OPTION>Mangore Orcsplitter, 41st Warrior of Black Isle<OPTION>Dewin gan'Bran, 48th Wizard of Black Isle<br></SELECT><br><font color=#80FFFF><I>Skating away on the thin ice of a new day.</I></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 2248<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/10/03 4:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ is dying</span><hr size=1> &gt;The fact you had to play an alt on a second account for a week, dident make fear hard. Although it did I suppose add risk. CR there was a matter of waiting a week and zoning in, theres no skill involved in that. <br>
